Threat Hunting Scenario: VILE Ransomware Security Tool Tampering - ETW Patch and Event Log Clear

In this threat hunting scenario, we searched for behavioral indicators associated with VILE ransomware defense evasion techniques, including Windows Event Log clearing, termination of security-related processes, and creation of ransomware-related files in common staging locations.

The objective was to identify attempts by attackers to disable security monitoring, remove forensic evidence, and prepare systems for ransomware execution. These activities may indicate an active compromise and could lead to successful ransomware deployment, data encryption, and operational disruption.

MITRE ATT&CK Mapping:

T1070.001 — Indicator Removal: Clear Windows Event Logs
T1562.001 — Impair Defenses: Disable or Modify System Security Tools
T1562.002 — Impair Defenses: Disable Windows Event Logging
T1486 — Data Encrypted for Impact
T1059.001 — Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell

